Then three of the bishops approach the altar. The candidate kneels down, and while two deacons hold the open book of the Gospels on his head, the presiding bishop recites a consecrating prayer, eucharistic in form, at the end of which comes the response, Amen.

The newly made bishop is then conducted to his seat, receives the kiss of peace, and then celebrates the Mass himself.
